BGP
 - The use of set clauses in outbound route maps can modify attributes and possibly 
   create routing loops. To avoid this behavior, most set clauses of outbound route 
   maps are ignored for routes reflected to iBGP peers. The only set clause of an 
   outbound route map on a route reflector (RR) that is acted upon is the set ip 
   next-hop clause. The set ip next-hop clause is applied to reflected routes.


